Simple TCPServer.

USAGE:
  $ ruby server.rb [hostname] [port]
  
hostname (optional parameter) - specifies hostname for server (default - localhost)
port (optional parameter) - specifies port for server (default - 4455)

RUNNING:
  Try start server in one terminal window and start ncat in another.
  E.g. $ ncat localhost 4455
  Type smth in ncat and server will print it.
  TIP: Type 'quit' (no quotes) to shutdown the server.
